datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Accepted
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date that the publisher accepted the resource into their system.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Available
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date the resource is made publicly available. May be a range.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Copyrighted
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The specific, documented date at which the resource receives a copyrighted status, if applicable.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Collected
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date or date range in which the resource content was collected.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Created
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date the resource itself was put together; this could refer to a timeframe in ancient history, a date range, or a single date for a final component, e.g., the finalised file with all the data.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Issued
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date that the resource is published or distributed, e.g., to a data centre

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Submitted
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date the creator submits the resource to the publisher. This could be different from Accepted if the publisher then applies a selection process.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Updated
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date of the last update to the resource, when the resource is being added to. May be a range.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Valid
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date or date range during which the dataset or resource is accurate.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Withdrawn
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date the resource is removed.

datasetDateTypeOptions.label: Controlled Access In Force
datasetDateTypeOptions.description: The date the resource is made available under controlled access of some form. May be a range. To indicate the end of such a period, use Available.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Contact Person
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person with knowledge of how to access, troubleshoot, or otherwise field issues related to the resource

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Data Collector
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person/institution responsible for finding or gathering/collecting data under the guidelines of the author(s) or Principal Investigator (PI)

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Data Curator
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person tasked with reviewing, enhancing, cleaning, or standardizing metadata and the associated data submitted for storage, use, and maintenance within a data centre or repository

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Data Manager
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person (or organisation with a staff of data managers, such as a data centre) responsible for maintaining the finished resource

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Distributor
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Institution tasked with responsibility to generate/disseminate copies of the resource in either electronic or print form

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Editor
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: A person who oversees the details related to the publication format of the resource

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Hosting Institution
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Typically, the organisation allowing the resource to be available on the internet through the provision of its hardware/software/operating support

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Producer
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Typically, a person or organisation responsible for the artistry and form of a media product

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Project Leader
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person officially designated as head of project team or sub-project team instrumental in the work necessary to development of the resource

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Project Manager
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person officially designated as manager of a project. Project may consist of one or many project teams and sub-teams.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Project Member
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person on the membership list of a designated project/project team

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Registration Agency
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Institution/organisation officially appointed by a Registration Authority to handle specific tasks within a defined area of responsibility

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Registration Authority
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: A standards-setting body from which Registration Agencies obtain official recognition and guidance

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Related Person
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: A person without a specifically defined role in the development of the resource, but who is someone the author wishes to recognize

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Researcher
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: A person involved in analysing data or the results of an experiment or formal study. May indicate an intern or assistant to one of the authors who helped with research but who was not so `key” as `o be listed as an author.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Research Group
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Typically refers to a group of individuals with a lab, department, or division that has a specifically defined focus of activity.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Rights Holder
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person or institution owning or managing property rights, including intellectual property rights over the resource

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Sponsor
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Person or organisation that issued a contract or under the auspices of which a work has been written, printed, published, developed, etc.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Supervisor
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Designated administrator over one or more groups/teams working to produce a resource, or over one or more steps of a development process

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Work Package Leader
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: A Work Package is a recognized data product, not all of which is included in publication. The package, instead, may include notes, discarded documents, etc. The Work Package Leader is

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Other
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Any person or institution making a significant contribution to the development and/or maintenance of the resource, but whose contribution is not adequately described by any of the other values for contributorType

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Study Lead
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: The individual who, if not the sponsor themselves, leads and co-ordinates the scientific and clinical activity within a clinical study, including co-ordinating the work of principal investigators at clinical sites. May be known as the Co-ordinating Investigator, the Study Chair, Study Director or similar terms.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Clinical Trial Site Principal Investigator
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: The individual responsible for the safe conduct of a clinical trial at a particular clinical site.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Clinical Study Manager
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An individual responsible for the operational management of a clinical study. Similar to a Project Manager but a study manager is heavily involved in the management of data and data collection.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Trial Sponsor
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: The organisation or individual that has the formal, legal role of a clinical trial sponsor, and is legally responsible for all aspects of a clinical trial.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Sponsor Contact
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An individual representing the sponsor and acting as an initial contact point.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Public Contact
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An individual designated as dealing with non-scientific queries from the public or press.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Recruitment Contact
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An individual designated as providing periodic updates on recruitment information or status, at all sites, usually for monitoring purposes.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Study Funder
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An organisation providing some or all of the additional funds required for the study.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Funder Contact
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An individual representing the funder and acting as an initial contact point.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Independent Monitoring Committee Member
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: A member of a safety monitoring committee for a clinical trial, independent of the researchers and research activity.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Medicinal Product Supplier
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation that provides one or more of the medicines investigated in a clinical study.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Medical Device Supplier
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation that provides one or more of the medical devices in a clinical study.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Logistics Support Organisation
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation that provides logistical input, e.g. provides a drug distribution service.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Scientific Support Organisation
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation that provides scientific support, e.g. a national or international research network.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Central Laboratory
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation that provides a central specialist laboratory testing facility..

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Central Imaging Facility
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation that provides a central specialist imaging or scanning facility.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Clinical Organisation
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation, usually a primary or secondary health care organisation, that manages one or more of the sites where a clinical study takes place.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Clinical Site
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: Organisation or location, usually in a primary or secondary health care organisation, that is one of the sites where a clinical study takes place.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Collaborating Organisation
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: May be listed as a secondary sponsor, an organisation other than the lead sponsor involved in supporting a study.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Sponsor Investigator
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: An individual with the role of sponsor as well as being the co-ordinating investigator for the study.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Results Contact
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: The individual, occasionally organisation, to be contacted for further information on the study results.

datasetContributorTypeOptions.label: Research Group Member
datasetContributorTypeOptions.description: From PubMed, an 'investigator' is an individual (e.g., collaborator or investigator) who is not an author of a paper but is listed as a member of a collective/corporate group that is an author of the paper.

datasetDeIdentTypeOptions.label: No De-identification
datasetDeIdentTypeOptions.description: Confirmed that no de-identification measures have been applied to the data set.

datasetDeIdentTypeOptions.label: De-identification Applied
datasetDeIdentTypeOptions.description: Some de-identification measures have been applied. Details should be described in comments and / or indicated in the linked boolean fields, or in separate documents.

datasetDeIdentTypeOptions.label: De-identification Applied & Primary Outcomes Re-assessed
datasetDeIdentTypeOptions.description: Some de-identification measures have been applied and are described. In addition the data has been re-analysed against the primary outcomes and the results described.

datasetConsentTypeOptions.label: No Explicit Consent
datasetConsentTypeOptions.description: No specific consent was given for the sharing of data or its re-use beyond the study in which it was originally collected.

datasetConsentTypeOptions.label: No Restriction
datasetConsentTypeOptions.description: No explicit restriction in the consent documents, though a broad consent to re-use is assumed, or this category is meaningless.

datasetConsentTypeOptions.label: General Research Use
datasetConsentTypeOptions.description: Consent indicates that use is allowed for general research use for any research purpose.

datasetConsentTypeOptions.label: Health Medical Biomedical Research
datasetConsentTypeOptions.description: Consent indicates that use is allowed for health/medical/biomedical purposes; does not include the study of population origins or ancestry, or the development of methods / algorithms (e.g. for ML)

datasetConsentTypeOptions.label: Disease Specific Research
datasetConsentTypeOptions.description: Consent indicates that use, for health / medical / biomedical research is allowed provided it is related to a specified disease (area). The disease (area) must be named or coded in the associated comments field.

datasetConsentTypeOptions.label: Consent Specified Not Elsewhere Categorised
datasetConsentTypeOptions.description: A descriptive statement regarding consent is available, but it does not fit into categories 1 - 5

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Public On Screen Access
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Completely open access on the web but content not available in any other format.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Public On Screen Access and Download
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Completely open access, material viewable and also directly available as a file download.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Public On Screen and API Access
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Completely open access, material viewable and also available through an API.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Public Download - Self Attestation Required
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Public and downloadable (only) once the user identifies and/or describes themselves.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Public On Screen Access - Self Attestation Required
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Public and viewable (only) once the user identifies and/or describes themselves.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Restricted Download
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: The user is an authenticated member of a defined group and can download the material (includes pay-walled journal articles).

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Restricted On Screen Access
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: The user is an authenticated member of a defined group but can only view the material. Analysis tools may be available.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Case By Case Download
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Based on a review of an individual request, often also requiring supporting documentation.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Case By Case On Screen Access
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: Based on a review of an individual request, often also requiring supporting documentation. Analysis tools may be available.

datasetAccessTypeOptions.label: Non Public Access - No Details
datasetAccessTypeOptions.description: The site asserts that the resource is not publicly available but provides no further details.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Audio-visual
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A series of visual representations imparting an impression of motion when shown in succession. May or may not include sound.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Book
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A medium for recording information in the form of writing or images, typically composed of many pages bound together and protected by a cover

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Book Chapter
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: One of the main divisions of a book.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Collection
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: An aggregation of resources, which may encompass collections of one resourceType as well as those of mixed types. A collection is described as a group; its parts may also be separately described.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Computational Notebook
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A virtual notebook environment used for literate programming

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Conference Paper
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: Article that is written with the goal of being accepted to a conference

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Conference Proceeding
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: Collection of  academic papers  published in the  context of an  academic conference

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Data Paper
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A factual and objective publication with a focused intent to identify and describe specific data, sets of data, or data collections to facilitate discoverability

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Dataset
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: Data encoded in a defined structure

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Dissertation
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A written essay,  treatise, or thesis, especially one written by a candidate for the degree of Doctor of Philosophy

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Event
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A non-persistent, time-based occurrence

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Image
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A visual representation other than text

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Interactive Resource
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A resource requiring interaction from the user to be understood, executed, or experienced

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Journal
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A scholarly  publication consisting of articles that is  published regularly throughout the year.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Journal Article
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A written composition on a topic of interest, which forms a separate part of a journal.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Model
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: An abstract, conceptual, graphical, mathematical or visualization model that represents empirical objects, phenomena, or physical processes

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Output Management Plan
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A formal document that outlines how  research outputs are to be handled both during a research  project and after the project is completed

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Peer Review
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: Evaluation of  scientific, academic, or professional work by others working in the same field

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Physical Object
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: An inanimate, three dimensional object or substance

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Preprint
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A version of a  scholarly or scientific paper that precedes formal peer review and publication in a peer-reviewed scholarly or scientific journal

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Report
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A document that presents information in an organized  format for a specific audience and purpose

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Service
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: An organized system of apparatus, appliances, staff, etc., for supplying some function(s) required by end users

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Software
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A computer program other than a computational notebook, in either source code (text) or compiled form. Use this type for general software components supporting scholarly research. Use the “ComputationalNoteb ook” value for virtual notebooks.

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Sound
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A resource primarily intended to be heard

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Standard
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: Something  established by  authority, custom, or general consent as a model, example, or point of reference

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Text
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A resource consisting primarily of words for reading that is not covered by any other textual resource type in this list

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Workflow
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: A structured series of steps which can be executed to produce a final outcome, allowing users a means to specify and enact their work in a more reproducible manner

datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.label: Other
datasetRelatedIdentifierResourceTypeOpti.description: If selected, supply a value for ResourceType.

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Cited By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that B includes A in a citation

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Cites
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that A includes B in a citation

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Supplement To
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that A is a supplement to B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Supplemented By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that B is a supplement to A

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Continued By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is continued by the work B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Continues
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a continuation of the work B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Describes
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A describes B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Described By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is described by B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Has Metadata
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates resource A has additional metadata B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Metadata For
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates additional metadata A for a resource B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Has Version
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A has a version (B)

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Version Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a version of B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is New Version Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a new edition of B, where the new edition has been modified or updated

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Previous Version Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a previous edition of B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Part Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a portion of B; may be used for elements of a series

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Ha sPart
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A includes the part B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Published In
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is published inside B, but is independent of other things published inside of B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Referenced By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is used as a source of information by B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: References
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates B is used as a source of information for A

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Documented By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates B is documentation about/ explaining A; e.g. points to software documentation

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Documents
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is documentation about B; e.g. points to software documentation

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Compiled By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates B is used to compile or create A

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Compiles
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates B is the result of a compile or creation event using  A

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Variant Form Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a variant or different form of B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Original Form Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is the original form of B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Identical To
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that A is identical to B, for use when there is a need to register two separate instances of the same resource

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Reviewed By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that A is reviewed by B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Reviews
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates that A is a review of B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Derived From
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates B is a source upon which A is based

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Source Of
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: indicates A is a source upon which B is based

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Required By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: Indicates A is required by B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Requires
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: Indicates A requires B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Obsoletes
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: Indicates A replaces B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Obsoleted By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: Indicates A is replaced by B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Is Collected By
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: Indicates A is collected by B

datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.label: Collects
datasetRelatedIdentifierRelationTypeOpti.description: Indicates A collects B

studyMetadataSponsorsResponsiblePartyTyp.description: An entity or organization that initiates the study.
studyMetadataSponsorsResponsiblePartyTyp.label: Sponsor

studyMetadataSponsorsResponsiblePartyTyp.description: The individual designated as a responsible party by the sponsor.
studyMetadataSponsorsResponsiblePartyTyp.label: Principal Investigator

studyMetadataSponsorsResponsiblePartyTyp.description: The individual who both initiates and conducts the study.
studyMetadataSponsorsResponsiblePartyTyp.label: Sponsor-Investigator

studyMetadataStudyTypeOptions.description: A clinical trial. Participants are assigned prospectively to an intervention or interventions according to a protocol to evaluate the effect of the intervention(s) on biomedical or other health related outcomes.
studyMetadataStudyTypeOptions.label: Interventional

studyMetadataStudyTypeOptions.description: Studies in human beings in which biomedical and/or health outcomes are assessed in pre-defined groups of individuals. Participants in the study may receive diagnostic, therapeutic, or other interventions, but the investigator does not assign specific interventions to the study participants. This includes when participants receive interventions as part of routine medical care, and a researcher studies the effect of the intervention.
studyMetadataStudyTypeOptions.label: Observational

studyMetadataStudyTypeOptions.description: An investigational drug product (including biological product) available through expanded access for patients who do not qualify for enrollment in a clinical trial. Expanded Access includes all expanded access types under section 561 of the Federal Food, Drug, and Cosmetic Act: (1) for individual patients, including emergency use; (2) for intermediate-size patient populations; and (3) under a treatment IND or treatment protocol. (For more information on data requirements for this Study Type, see Expanded Access Data Element $defs).
studyMetadataStudyTypeOptions.label: Expanded Access

studyMetadataAllocationOptions.description: Participants are assigned to intervention groups by chance.
studyMetadataAllocationOptions.label: Randomized

studyMetadataAllocationOptions.description: Participants are expressly assigned to intervention groups through a non-random method, such as physician choice.
studyMetadataAllocationOptions.label: Non-randomized

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions are being evaluated for treating a disease, syndrome, or condition.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Treatment

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions are being assessed for preventing the development of a specific disease or health condition.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Prevention

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions are being evaluated for identifying a disease or health condition.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Diagnostic

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions are evaluated for maximizing comfort, minimizing side effects, or mitigating against a decline in the participant's health or function.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Supportive Care

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions are assessed or examined for identifying a condition, or risk factors for a condition, in people who are not yet known to have the condition or risk factor.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Screening

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions for evaluating the delivery, processes, management, organization, or financing of healthcare.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Health Services Research

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: One or more interventions for examining the basic mechanism of action (for example, physiology or biomechanics of an intervention).
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Basic Science

studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.description: An intervention of a device product is being evaluated in a small clinical trial (generally fewer than 10 participants) to determine the feasibility of the product, or a clinical trial to test a prototype device for feasibility and not health outcomes.
studyMetadataInterventionModelOptions.label: Device Feasibility

studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.description: Clinical trials with a single arm.
studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.label: Single Group Assignment

studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.description: Participants are assigned to one of two or more groups in parallel for the duration of the study.
studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.label: Parallel Assignment

studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.description: Participants receive one of two (or more) alternative interventions during the initial phase of the study and receive the other intervention during the second phase of the study.
studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.label: Crossover Assignment

studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.description: Two or more interventions, each alone and in combination, are evaluated in parallel against a control group.
studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.label: Factorial Assignment

studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.description: Groups of participants are assigned to receive interventions based on prior milestones being reached in the study, such as in some dose escalation and adaptive design studies.
studyMetadataPrimaryPurposeOptions.label: Sequential Assignment

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Study halted prematurely, prior to enrollment of the first participant.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Withdrawn

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Participants are currently being recruited, whether or not any participants have yet been enrolled.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Recruiting

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Study is continuing, meaning participants are receiving an intervention or being examined, but new participants are not currently being recruited or enrolled.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Active, not recruiting

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Participants are not yet being recruited.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Not yet recruiting

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Study halted prematurely but potentially will resume.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Suspended

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Participants are being (or will be) selected from a predetermined population.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Enrolling by invitation

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: The study has concluded normally; participants are no longer receiving an intervention or being examined (that is, last participant's last visit has occurred).
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Completed

studyMetadataStatusOptions.description: Study halted prematurely and will not resume; participants are no longer being examined or receiving intervention.
studyMetadataStatusOptions.label: Terminated
